\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.1}{\ignorespaces Architecture of the simulation engine showing the data flow from Simulator::run() through DeviceFactory and AnalysisManager to the individual analysis handlers, with the shared solver infrastructure.}}{53}{figure.6.1}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.2}{\ignorespaces KLU solver four-phase lifecycle within the Newton-Raphson iteration. The first iteration performs analyse + factorise, while subsequent iterations reuse the symbolic ordering via refactorise.}}{57}{figure.6.2}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.3}{\ignorespaces Newton-Raphson convergence for a common-source NMOS amplifier with source degeneration. The drain voltage converges from the initial guess (0~V) to the operating point (~3.16~V) in 6 iterations.}}{59}{figure.6.3}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.4}{\ignorespaces GMIN geometric reduction schedule across 10 steps. Each GMIN value (log scale) is solved to convergence, seeding the next step.}}{60}{figure.6.4}%
